### Change image quality

- References:
https://askubuntu.com/questions/1164/how-to-easily-resize-images-via-command-line#13825

https://thelinuxcode.com/imagemagick-resize-image/

https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/reduce-file-size-of-images-linux

- Commands:

/* resize image */
mogrify -resize 320x240 *.jpg
mogrify -resize 320x240! *.jpg
mogrify -resize 10% *.jpg

/* reduce quality */
mogrify -quality 80% *.jpg


### Mass rename

see: https://www.makeuseof.com/batch-rename-files-in-linux/

-> Use Thunar "bulk rename" utility. Select all files, right click -> rename


